    "# Skip loop cycle using `continue` statement\n",
    "\n",
    "The continue statement is another control flow statement in Python that is used within loops to skip the rest of the current iteration (cycle) of the loop and move on to the next iteration. In simpler terms, it allows you to skip over certain parts of a loop when a particular condition is met."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Example: loop with continue statement\n",
    "\n",
    "number = 0\n",
    "while number < 10:\n",
    "    number += 1\n",
    "    # if number is 5 skip this cycle.\n",
    "    if number == 5:\n",
    "        continue\n",
    "    print(number)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# `while` loop with `else` statement\n",
    "\n",
    "While loops in python can be used with else statement to execute some code when condition is False."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Example: while loop with else statement\n",
    "\n",
    "number = 0\n",
    "# if number is less than 5, execute loops body\n",
    "while number < 5:\n",
    "    print(number)\n",
    "    number += 1\n",
    "# if number is more or equal to 5, execute else body\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"end of the loop\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "❗ Important to note that `else` statement can be used only when loop end naturally, and can not be used when loop was ended with `break` statement."
   ]
  },
